name: wood preservative production, organic salts, Cr-free, outdoor use, ground contact | wood preservative, organic salt, Cr-free | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/11755/documentation

According to EN 335-1:2005, five use classes are distinguished for chemical wood protection based on the general exposure of wood in its application, wetting regime in service and the biological agents to be expected. This exposure scenario determines the potentially vulnerable zone of wood and the required treatment for the application of the wood preservative (see table)

From reception of chemicals at the factory gate

The dataset covers the components and preparation of a typical water-based/organic solvent based [as applicable] wood preservative for the use class according to EN 335-1:2006 as indicated in the name of the dataset, ready to be packed. In addition it contains an estimate for electricity consumption and for infrastructure. Packaging is not included. It is assumed that the production process does not generate any waste water.
